    <h2>The Build and Make of StockIT</h2>
    <h3>Overview of the Technologies Used</h3>
    <p>
        StockIT is built using ASP.NET Core and Razor Pages, leveraging the power and flexibility of these technologies
        to create a robust and user-friendly web application. The project targets the .NET 8.0 framework, as indicated in the
        StockIT.csproj and StockIT.BLL.csproj files, ensuring that we are using the latest features and improvements offered by .NET.
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>ASP.NET Core: Chosen for its high performance and ability to handle high levels of traffic, ASP.NET Core serves as the backbone of our web application.</li>
        <li>Razor Pages: Used for creating dynamic web pages that interact seamlessly with our backend logic. Razor Pages make it easier to write clean, maintainable code by keeping the HTML markup and C# processing code together.</li>
        <li>Entity Framework Core: For data access, we've utilized Entity Framework Core, which allows for a code-first approach to database development. This ORM framework simplifies data manipulation and ensures our application is scalable.</li>
    </ul>

